{
  "texts": [
    "It reflects a long-standing competition with the U.S. in the tech sector that has previously led to product and company bans and constant disputes on espionage [Girishankar, 2024; Pan et al., 2024].",
    "China has, furthermore, surpassed the U.S. claim to global dominance in various sectors, reinforcing the ongoing rivalry [Lippert & Perthes, 2020].",
    "While Europe is considered part of the West, the discourse seems less polarised and rife with black-and-white positioning.",
    "Although this imaginary has become relevant again with the current AI summer, the AI race imaginary has an expansive history debating similar issues, implications and possibilities.",
    "Considering that these AI imaginaries are historically informed and political, it is important to question the implications of this geopolitical tension."
  ]
}